race.comment: JAM PACKED (2) is consistent without winning hitting the top-five in all seven career efforts to date but this is not an overly strong affair. Lerena sticks in the saddle following the last couple of runner-up finishes and can go one better against this lot. STOICISM (3) has hit the frame at the past three starts including placing over this track and trip three back. Looms as the main danger. LA GRACIA (4) will be ready to peak now third-up from the break and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Top-three candidate. EFFIE'S JOY (5) has gotten better with each run this time in and looks to be working up to a maiden victory. In the mix. The well-related WEEKEND ARTIST (6) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed I'm All The Talk) best of the rest.
